{"nodes":[{"content":"Configuring the Local Configuration Manager","pos":[13,56]},{"content":"Configuring the Local Configuration Manager","pos":[201,244]},{"content":"Applies To: Windows PowerShell 5.0","pos":[248,282]},{"content":"The Local Configuration Manager (LCM) is the engine of Windows PowerShell Desired State Configuration (DSC).","pos":[284,392]},{"content":"The LCM runs on every target node, and is responsible for parsing and enacting configurations that are sent to the node.","pos":[393,513]},{"content":"It is also responsible for a number of other aspects of DSC, including the following.","pos":[514,599]},{"content":"Determining refresh mode (push or pull).","pos":[603,643]},{"content":"Specifying how often a node pulls and enacts configurations.","pos":[646,706]},{"content":"Associating the node with pull servers.","pos":[709,748]},{"content":"Specifying partial configurations.","pos":[751,785]},{"content":"You use a special type of configuration to configure the LCM to specify each of these behaviors.","pos":[787,883]},{"content":"The following sections describe how to configure the LCM.","pos":[884,941]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: This topic applies to the LCM introduced in Windows PowerShell 5.0.","pos":[945,1022]},{"content":"For information about configuring the LCM in Windows PowerShell 4.0, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows PowerShell 4.0 Desired State Configuration Local Configuration Manager<ept id=\"p1\">](metaconfig4.md)</ept>.","pos":[1023,1193]},{"content":"Writing and enacting an LCM configuration","pos":[1198,1239]},{"content":"To configure the LCM, you create and run a special type of configuration.","pos":[1241,1314]},{"content":"To specify an LCM configuration, you use the DscLocalConfigurationManager attribute.","pos":[1315,1399]},{"content":"The following shows a simple configuration that sets the LCM to push mode.","pos":[1400,1474]},{"content":"You call and run the configuration to create the configuration MOF, just as you would a normal configuration (for information on creating the configuration MOF, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Compiling the configuration<ept id=\"p1\">](configurations.md#compiling-the-configuration)</ept>).","pos":[1658,1901]},{"content":"Unlike normal configurations, you do not enact an LCM configuration by calling the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn521623.aspx)</ept> cmdlet.","pos":[1902,2077]},{"content":"Instead, you call the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Set-DscLocalConfigurationManager<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn521621.aspx)</ept> cmdlet, supplying the path to the configuration MOF as a parameter.","pos":[2078,2262]},{"content":"After you enact the configuration, you can see the properties of the LCM by calling the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Get-DscLocalConfigurationManager<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn407378.aspx)</ept> cmdlet.","pos":[2263,2453]},{"content":"An LCM configuration can contain blocks only for a limited set of resources.","pos":[2455,2531]},{"content":"In the previous example, the only resource called is <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[2532,2598]},{"content":"The other available resources are:","pos":[2599,2633]},{"pos":[2637,2718],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ConfigurationRepositoryWeb<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: specifies an HTTP pull server for configurations."},{"pos":[2722,2804],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ConfigurationRepositoryShare<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: specifies an SMB pull server for configurations."},{"pos":[2807,2876],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ResourceRepositoryWeb<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: specifies an HTTP pull server for modules."},{"pos":[2879,2949],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ResourceRepositoryShare<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: specifies an SMB pull server for modules."},{"pos":[2952,3029],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ReportServerWeb<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: specifies an HTTP pull server to which reports are sent."},{"pos":[3032,3091],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>PartialConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: specifies partial configurations."},{"content":"Basic settings","pos":[3096,3110]},{"content":"Other than specifying pull servers and partial configurations, all of the properties of the LCM are configured in a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> block.","pos":[3112,3247]},{"content":"The following properties are available in a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> block.","pos":[3248,3311]},{"content":"Property","pos":[3316,3324]},{"content":"Type","pos":[3329,3333]},{"content":"Description","pos":[3338,3349]},{"content":"ConfigurationModeFrequencyMins","pos":[3399,3429]},{"content":"UInt32","pos":[3431,3437]},{"content":"How often, in minutes, the current configuration is checked and applied.","pos":[3439,3511]},{"content":"This property is ignored if the ConfigurationMode property is set to ApplyOnly.","pos":[3512,3591]},{"content":"The default value is 15.","pos":[3592,3616]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>Note<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept>: Either the value of this property must be a multiple of the value of the <bpt id=\"p2\">__</bpt>RefreshFrequencyMins<ept id=\"p2\">__</ept> property, or the value of the <bpt id=\"p3\">__</bpt>RefreshFrequencyMins<ept id=\"p3\">__</ept> property must be a multiple of the value of this property.","pos":[3622,3843]},{"content":"RebootNodeIfNeeded","pos":[3848,3866]},{"content":"bool","pos":[3868,3872]},{"content":"Set this to <bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>$true<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept> to automatically reboot the node after a configuration that requires reboot is applied.","pos":[3874,3983]},{"content":"Otherwise, you will have to manually reboot the node for any configuration that requires it.","pos":[3984,4076]},{"content":"The default value is <bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>$false<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept>.","pos":[4077,4109]},{"content":"ConfigurationMode","pos":[4114,4131]},{"content":"string","pos":[4133,4139]},{"content":"Specifies how the LCM actually applies the configuration to the target nodes.","pos":[4142,4219]},{"content":"Possible values are <bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>\"ApplyOnly\"<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept>,<bpt id=\"p2\">__</bpt>\"ApplyandMonitior\"(default)<ept id=\"p2\">__</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p3\">__</bpt>\"ApplyandAutoCorrect\"<ept id=\"p3\">__</ept>.","pos":[4220,4319]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>ApplyOnly<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept>: DSC applies the configuration and does nothing further unless a new configuration is pushed to the target node or when a new configuration is pulled from a server.","pos":[4328,4506]},{"content":"After initial application of a new configuration, DSC does not check for drift from a previously configured state.","pos":[4507,4621]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>ApplyAndMonitor<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept>: This is the default value.","pos":[4631,4678]},{"content":"The LCM applies any new configurations.","pos":[4679,4718]},{"content":"After initial application of a new configuration, if the target node drifts from the desired state, DSC reports the discrepancy in logs.","pos":[4719,4855]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>ApplyAndAutoCorrect<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept>: DSC applies any new configurations.","pos":[4864,4924]},{"content":"After initial application of a new configuration, if the target node drifts from the desired state, DSC reports the discrepancy in logs, and then re-applies the current configuration.","pos":[4925,5108]},{"content":"ActionAfterReboot","pos":[5123,5140]},{"content":"string","pos":[5142,5148]},{"content":"Specifies what happens after a reboot during the application of a configuration.","pos":[5150,5230]},{"content":"The possible values are <bpt id=\"p1\">__</bpt>\"ContinueConfiguration(default)\"<ept id=\"p1\">__</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">__</bpt>\"StopConfiguration\"<ept id=\"p2\">__</ept>.","pos":[5231,5320]},{